<td><strong>September Camping Trip To Tofino/Ucluelet</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<!-- blank -->
<td><img src="http://www.ams.ubc.ca/clubs/surfclub/surfclub2006/travel/Tofino%202.jpg"></td>
<!-- description -->
<td>Every September the week after club week we go on a camping trip to <a href="http://www.surfjunction.com/" title="Surf Junction Campground">Surf Junction Campground</a>.
The campground has a sweet hot tub, cost is usually around $150 and it includes transportation to/from the campground and beaches, one dinner, beer, surfboard rentals, and camping.
This trip can accommodate pretty much as many people as we desire, were looking into renting the whole campground along w/ the Uvic surf club, stay tuned, itll be a gong show regardless.
</td>
</tr>
<td>&nbsp;</td>
<td><strong>Westport Trips</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<!-- <td><%#= image_tag "westport1.jpg", :height => 130 -%></td> -->
<td><%= image_tag "westport_wave.jpg", :height => 130 -%></td>
<td>In October and November we go on several bare bones trips (ie no we dont take care of rentals) to Westport Washington that are geared for more experienced surfers (ie we dont take care of rentals).
Wesport is an interesting place w/ a bit of a pirate fetish, but the waves are generally bigger than Tofino and can be really clean as well.
We usually stay in a super nice motel (<%= link_to "sarcasm", "http://maps.google.ca/maps?ie=UTF-8&oe=utf-8&rls=org.mozilla:en-US:official&client=firefox-a&um=1&q=cranberry+motel+westport+washington&fb=1&view=text&latlng=4604443846064334852" -%>) that ends up being about $10 per night per person; combine that with not having to pay for the ferry and US gas prices these trips end up being our most economical.  
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>&nbsp;</td>
<td><strong>October Tofino Trips</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><img src="http://www.ams.ubc.ca/clubs/surfclub/surfclub2006/travel/house.jpg"></td>
<td>In late September and in October we offer two to three trips back to tofino.  We usually stay in the <a href="http://www.surfsinn.ca/" title="Surfs Inn">Surfs Inn </a>
which can accommodate around twenty people.  These trips usually cost a bit more (like $190 or so) and include all the same stuff as the camping trip.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>&nbsp;</td>
<td><strong>Reading Break Trip</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><img src="http://www.ams.ubc.ca/clubs/surfclub/surfclub2006/travel/800px-Palms_El_Salvador.JPG"></td>
<td>Every year we have a big reading break trip.  Past trips have gone to costa rica and various places in Mexico.  
This year we are researching El Salvador, Nicaragua, Panama, and as a last restort we will try to get back to <a href="http://www.malpaissurfcamp.com/" title="Mal Pais Surf Camp">Mal Pais Surf Camp</a>
in Mal Pais, Costa Rica.  The club traveled to Mal Pais in 2005 and it was an amazing trip, we cant go wrong heading there.  If anybody has an experience, thoughts, insisght on any of these potential locations send us an email, wed love to hear your thoughts/experiences.
The trips usually costs around $1000 and it always covers airfare and boarding;  It may also cover board rentals, it depends on where we are staying.
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>&nbsp;</td>
